<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore
                    of the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13027d8">Figure 138</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install the O-ring in the
                    tower groove.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13027d8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13027d8" filename="../figg13/G13027d8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 138. Install Spade Pin in Bore of Housing Tower</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot
                    and install the tension spring washer over the ball, dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13027d9">Figure 139</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13027d9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13027d9" filename="../figg13/G13027d9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 139. Install Tension Spring Washer Over Ball</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing,
                    <emph type="bold">seating one coil at a time</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13027e0">Figure 140</hotlnk>)
                    <emph type="bold">.</emph>
                    Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13027e0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13027e0" filename="../figg13/G13027e0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 140. Install Tension Spring Under Lugs in Housing</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13027e1">Figure 141</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f13027e1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13027e1" filename="../figg13/G13027e1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 141. Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
